`mech test`
===============================================================================

`mech test` runs source files and validates invariants.

An invariant is a top-level binding whose name ends in `!` and whose expression evaluates to `bool`.

```mech
x := 1
positive! := x > 0
```

1. Run tests
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

```sh
mech test .
mech test tests/example.mec
```

2. Output files
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Write JSON output:

```sh
mech test . --out report.json
```

Write Mech record output:

```sh
mech test . --out report.mec
```

3. Verbose output
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

```sh
mech test . --verbose
```

Verbose output includes detail for passed invariants as well as failed invariants.

See [Validation](../validation.html) for invariant syntax and report shape.
